quran[17]{c,v,t}:
  19,66,"Yet ňĻsomeňļ people ask ňĻmockinglyňļ, ‚ÄúAfter I die, will I really be raised to life again?‚ÄĚ"
  19,67,"Do ňĻsuchňļ people not remember that We created them before, when they were nothing"
  19,68,"By your Lord ňĻO Prophetňļ! We will surely gather them along with the devils, and then set them around Hell on their knees"
  19,69,Then We will certainly begin by dragging out of every group the ones most defiant to the Most Compassionate
  19,70,And We truly know best who is most deserving of burning in it
  19,71,There is none of you who will not pass over it.¬†ňĻThis isňļ a decree your Lord must fulfil
  19,72,"Then We will deliver those who were devout, leaving the wrongdoers there on their knees"
  19,73,"When Our clear revelations are recited to them, the disbelievers ask the believers ňĻmockinglyňļ, ‚ÄúWhich of the two of us is better in status and superior in assembly?‚ÄĚ"
  19,74,"ňĻImagine, O Prophetňļ how many peoples We have destroyed before them, who were far better in luxury and splendour"
  19,75,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúWhoever is ňĻentrenchedňļ in misguidance, the Most Compassionate will allow them plenty of time, until‚ÄĒbehold!‚ÄĒthey face what they are threatened with: either the torment or the Hour. Only then will they realize who is worse in position and inferior in manpower.‚ÄĚ"
  19,76,And God increases in guidance those who are ňĻrightlyňļ guided. And the everlasting good deeds are far better with your Lord in reward and in outcome
  19,77,"Have you seen ňĻO Prophetňļ the one¬†who rejects Our revelations yet boasts, ‚ÄúI will definitely be granted ňĻplenty ofňļ wealth and children ňĻif there is an afterlifeňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  19,78,Has he looked into the unseen or taken a pledge from the Most Compassionate
  19,79,Not at all! We certainly record whatever he claims and will increase his punishment extensively
  19,80,"And We will inherit what he boasts of, and he will come before Us all by himself"
  19,81,"They have taken other gods, instead of God, seeking strength ňĻand protectionňļ through them"
  19,82,But no! Those ňĻgodsňļ will deny their worship and turn against them